# INSIGHTS

[INSIGHT-1]
type: success
description: Keeping the parser dependency-free reduced adoption friction — third-party integrations appeared within weeks of the spec being published.
confidence: 0.92
source: T-INT-002
related_tasks: T-INT-001, T-INT-002

[INSIGHT-2]
type: observation
description: The v1 checkbox task format is sufficient for simple documents, but teams with 20+ tasks strongly prefer the v2 block format for its metadata richness.
confidence: 0.78
source: community-feedback

[INSIGHT-3]
type: success
description: Placing SUMMARY first in the LLM context window significantly improved the quality of AI-generated TASKS and INSIGHTS by giving the model an immediate state snapshot.
confidence: 0.88
source: INSIGHT-1
related_tasks: T-INT-003

# DECISIONS

[DEC-1]
choice: Use a single .mrcf file as the project source of truth rather than many loosely related markdown files
reason: Reduces cognitive overhead for both humans and LLMs; all context in one place means AI always has the full picture
alternatives: Multi-file wiki, separate spec + plan + task files
impact: high
date: 2026-03-01

[DEC-2]
choice: Keep the parser dependency-free
reason: Third parties can reimplement the parser in any language without pulling a dependency tree; lowers adoption barrier
alternatives: Use unified/remark, gray-matter, or a YAML library
impact: medium
date: 2026-03-05

[DEC-3]
choice: Add four optional v2 sections (SUMMARY, INSIGHTS, DECISIONS, REFERENCES) rather than extending the five required sections
reason: Preserves backward compatibility with v1 documents; optional sections can be added incrementally as projects mature
alternatives: Replace TASKS with a richer block system, add metadata directly to existing sections
impact: high
date: 2026-03-20

# REFERENCES

